<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A 43-year-old woman burst into a house and assaulted the occupant in an explosive row over her granddaughter. </p>

<p>Lisa Marie Wesley marched into the Queensland home and grabbed a woman by the arm after the argument erupted on January 30, resulting in bruises and lacerations. </p>

<p>Ms Wesley plead guilty to one count of assault occasioning bodily harm on Friday at Caboolture Magistrate's Court, according to the Caboolture Shire Herald. </p>

<p>Lisa Marie Wesley (pictured) marched into the Queensland home and grabbed a woman by the arm after the row erupted on January 30 resulting in bruises and lacerations </p>

<p>'You have to be careful ... because these things can escalate from nought to 100,' Magistrate Andrew Hackett warned the woman. </p>

<p>He also noted the incident was one that 'speaks of high emotion'. </p>

<p>She did not have a conviction recorded but was fined $500 after the guilty plea. </p>

<p>'Had you had prior convictions for violence, I would have recorded a conviction,' Magistrate Hackett said. </p>

